== Comma-merge ==
First, let's work through an example of a comma-merge across domain bases: meantone <math>\mathrm{C}_1</math> with archytas <math>\mathrm{C}_2</math>, where meantone is in the 5-limit standard domain basis 2.3.5, which we'll call <math>B_1</math>, and archytas is in the 2.3.7 domain basis, which we'll call <math>B_2</math>.

First we must merge these two temperaments' domain bases. Concatenate them to 2.3.5.2.3.7, then convert to matrix:


<math>

\begin{array} {ccc}

