Now, let's work through an example of a map-merge of temperaments with different basis elements: 22 equal temperament <math>M_1</math> with 17 equal temperament <math>M_2</math>, where 22-ET has domain basis 2.3.5.11, which we'll call <math>B_1</math>, and 17-ET has domain basis 2.9.7.11, which we'll call <math>B_2</math>.

